   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>ASSURANCE OF SALVATION</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>We are God s children.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The salvation which we received from the Lord is precious and secure.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>This salvation was received at the moment we believed, and it will never be lost.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Once we are saved, we are eternally saved.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>I. KNOWING THAT YOU ARE SAVED BY BELIEVING</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>John 6:47 says:</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Truly, truly, I say to you, he who believes in Me has eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>BY CALLING</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Romans 10:13 says:</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>For, Whoever calls upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>BY BEING BAPTIZED</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Mark 16:16 says:</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>He who believes and is baptized shall be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Since you have believed, called, and been baptized, by the Word of God you can know assuredly that you are saved.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>THE ASSURANCE OF SALVATION</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Not only can we know about our salvation, but we can be assured of it as well.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>SAVED AT THE MOMENT WE BELIEVED</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>He who hears My word and believes Him who sent Me has eternal life, and will not come into judgment, but has passed out of death into life.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>John 5:24</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>WE CAN KNOW THAT WE ARE SAVED</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>I write these things to you that you may know that you have eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>1 John 5:13</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>HOW TO KNOW THAT WE ARE SAVED 1.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>THE INNER WITNESS</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>THE SPIRIT OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The Spirit Himself witnesses with our spirit that we are the children of God.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Romans 8:16</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>No wonder that when we call our God Abba, Father! we feel so natural and sweet.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>And because you are sons, God sent forth the Spirit of His Son into our hearts, crying, Abba, Father!</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Galatians 4:6</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>THE OUTER WITNESS</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>THE WORD OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>I write these things to you that you may know that you have eternal life, to you who believe in the name of the Son of God.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>1 John 5:13</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>The words of the Bible are the title deed of our eternal salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>They are our guarantee and surety.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>This is like buying a house.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>After you make your payment you obtain the title deed, and the house is yours.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>It is not a matter of feeling or opinion, but an accomplished fact.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>THE PROOF OF</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>THE EXPERIENCE OF LIFE</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>1 Loving the brothers</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>We know that we have passed out of death into life, because we love the brothers.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>1 John 3:14</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>2 Feeling sorry about our sins</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>And if anyone sins, we have an Advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the Righteous.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>1 John 2:1</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>It is possible for regenerated believers to sin if they do not live by the divine life.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>When we sin, our fellowship with God is broken, and we will feel darkened, uneasy, and sorry.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>III.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>THE SECURITY OF SALVATION</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Our salvation is secure, because this salvation is safeguarded by:</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>THE LOVE OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>Having loved His own who were in the world, He loved them to the uttermost.</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>John 13:1</S>
   <S PAR='61' RSNT='1' SNO='61'>The love with which God loves us is an eternal love; it is a love that loves us to the uttermost.</S>
   <S PAR='62' RSNT='1' SNO='62'>It will not cease regardless of our condition.</S>
   <S PAR='63' RSNT='1' SNO='63'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='64' RSNT='1' SNO='64'>THE POWER OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='65' RSNT='1' SNO='65'>And I give to them eternal life, and they shall by no means perish forever, and no one shall snatch them out of My hand.</S>
   <S PAR='66' RSNT='1' SNO='66'>John 10:28</S>
   <S PAR='67' RSNT='1' SNO='67'>The hand of God is a mighty hand.</S>
   <S PAR='68' RSNT='1' SNO='68'>It will keep us from falling.</S>
   <S PAR='69' RSNT='1' SNO='69'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='70' RSNT='1' SNO='70'>THE REDEMPTION OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='71' RSNT='1' SNO='71'>He is able to save to the uttermost those who come forward to God through Him.</S>
   <S PAR='72' RSNT='1' SNO='72'>Hebrews 7:25</S>
   <S PAR='73' RSNT='1' SNO='73'>The Lord lives forever, and He will save us to the uttermost.</S>
   <S PAR='74' RSNT='1' SNO='74'>After we are saved, although our feeling and condition may change, the fact and position of our salvation will never change.</S>
   <S PAR='75' RSNT='1' SNO='75'>Once we are saved we are eternally saved, eternally perfected, and will not perish eternally.</S>
   <S PAR='76' RSNT='1' SNO='76'>IV.</S>
   <S PAR='77' RSNT='1' SNO='77'>THE RESULT OF SALVATION</S>
   <S PAR='78' RSNT='1' SNO='78'>CLEARANCE OF THE PAST</S>
   <S PAR='79' RSNT='1' SNO='79'>After a believer is saved, he should spontaneously terminate the things of the past.</S>
   <S PAR='80' RSNT='1' SNO='80'>This is the practice of a believer who is clearly saved.</S>
   <S PAR='81' RSNT='1' SNO='81'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='82' RSNT='1' SNO='82'>FORSAKING THE IDOLS</S>
   <S PAR='83' RSNT='1' SNO='83'>You turned to God from idols to serve a living and true God.</S>
   <S PAR='84' RSNT='1' SNO='84'>1 Thessalonians 1:9</S>
   <S PAR='85' RSNT='1' SNO='85'>Any idols or things related to idols must be thoroughly dealt with.</S>
   <S PAR='86' RSNT='1' SNO='86'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='87' RSNT='1' SNO='87'>DESTROYING THE EVIL AND</S>
   <S PAR='88' RSNT='1' SNO='88'>DEMONIC THINGS</S>
   <S PAR='89' RSNT='1' SNO='89'>And a considerable number of those who practiced magic brought their books together and burned them before all.</S>
   <S PAR='90' RSNT='1' SNO='90'>Acts 19:19</S>
   <S PAR='91' RSNT='1' SNO='91'>All inappropriate items and improper books, pictures, and apparatuses should be properly dealt with.</S>
   <S PAR='92' RSNT='1' SNO='92'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='93' RSNT='1' SNO='93'>RESTORING TO OTHERS WHAT WE OWE</S>
   <S PAR='94' RSNT='1' SNO='94'>And Zaccheus stood and said to the Lord, Behold, the half of my possessions, Lord, I give to the poor; and if I have taken anything from anyone by false accusations, I restore four times as much.</S>
   <S PAR='95' RSNT='1' SNO='95'>Luke 19:8</S>
   <S PAR='96' RSNT='1' SNO='96'>Whatever we have obtained by way of extortion, cheating, stealing, or any other improper means must be returned or dealt with.</S>
   <S PAR='97' RSNT='1' SNO='97'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='98' RSNT='1' SNO='98'>TERMINATING THE OLD WAY OF LIFE</S>
   <S PAR='99' RSNT='1' SNO='99'>We must pray to the Lord concerning our past conduct, behavior, and way of living.</S>
   <S PAR='100' RSNT='1' SNO='100'>Anything that does not correspond to the grace of our calling, or anything that is not fitting for saints, should be terminated.</S>
   <S PAR='101' RSNT='1' SNO='101'>Walk worthily of the calling with which you were called.</S>
   <S PAR='102' RSNT='1' SNO='102'>Ephesians 4:1</S>
   <S PAR='103' RSNT='1' SNO='103'>Praise the Lord that at the start of your new life you can know clearly that you are definitely saved and be led to have a clear termination of your past so that you can have an entirely new living.</S>
   </TEXT>
